President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Richard S. Tischner of Virginia as the Director of the Agency for the District of Columbia Court Services and Offender Supervision for a six-year term. Tischner currently serves as an Assistant United States Attorney and the Chief of the Superior Court Division at the United States Attorney's Office for the District of Columbia. He has over 33 years of experience as an attorney in the United States Federal Government, including 30 years as an Assistant United States Attorney at the Department of Justice. Tischner has also worked as an attorney for the Merit Systems Protection Board and the Federal Trade Commission.